1
00:00:10,916 --> 00:00:13,291
♪

2
00:00:14,375 --> 00:00:16,875
[footsteps approaching]

3
00:00:19,541 --> 00:00:22,583
[DANNY]
Ah. You're still alive.

4
00:00:22,666 --> 00:00:24,833
And so weak.

5
00:00:26,083 --> 00:00:28,166
Shall I put you out
of your misery?

6
00:00:31,250 --> 00:00:32,958
Well, Zack?

7
00:00:35,041 --> 00:00:37,166
Oh, dear, did I wake you?

8
00:00:37,250 --> 00:00:39,375
Just as friendly as ever, I see.

9
00:00:39,458 --> 00:00:41,875
I'm impressed you can
even move in that state.

10
00:00:41,958 --> 00:00:45,666
How in the hell are you
still alive, you freak?

11
00:00:45,750 --> 00:00:47,208
Are you surprised?

12
00:00:47,291 --> 00:00:49,583
I knew all along that you'd try
to hunt Rachel down

13
00:00:49,666 --> 00:00:51,000
and get past my floor.

14
00:00:51,083 --> 00:00:53,291
You couldn't be more obvious.

15
00:00:53,375 --> 00:00:55,875
And since I had you
all figured out,

16
00:00:55,958 --> 00:00:58,666
I took some minor
safety precautions.

17
00:00:58,750 --> 00:01:01,208
Though, you still
slashed me open.

18
00:01:01,291 --> 00:01:04,791
Then I'll just have to make sure
to finish the job this time!

19
00:01:04,875 --> 00:01:08,041
[groaning]

20
00:01:08,125 --> 00:01:13,500
Careful, or you'll bleed out.
Trust me. I know first-hand.

21
00:01:13,583 --> 00:01:16,166
You did quite a number
on me last time we met.

22
00:01:16,250 --> 00:01:20,041
Funny. You're lookin'
pretty damn healthy to me.

23
00:01:20,125 --> 00:01:24,250
Well, I am a doctor, you know.
Not some idiot like you.

24
00:01:24,333 --> 00:01:28,083
So I treated my wounds.
But even so, I'm exhausted.

25
00:01:28,166 --> 00:01:30,791
I saw the opportunity
to decapitate you in your sleep,

26
00:01:30,875 --> 00:01:32,291
but then you woke up.

27
00:01:32,375 --> 00:01:33,708
Spoiled my fun.

28
00:01:33,791 --> 00:01:35,708
Say, aren't you and Rachel

29
00:01:35,791 --> 00:01:37,666
supposed to be wandering
around together?

30
00:01:37,750 --> 00:01:41,125
And if not, then tell me
where she is right now.

31
00:01:42,750 --> 00:01:44,791
Oh, man,
you're an even bigger moron

32
00:01:44,875 --> 00:01:46,375
than I thought you were.

33
00:01:46,458 --> 00:01:48,833
You don't seriously think
I'm gonna tell you where she is,

34
00:01:48,916 --> 00:01:50,208
do you, doctor boy?

35
00:01:50,291 --> 00:01:52,041
And what if I tell you
I already killed her?

36
00:01:52,125 --> 00:01:54,375
Whatcha gonna do then, huh?

37
00:01:55,708 --> 00:01:57,333
[scoffs]

38
00:01:57,416 --> 00:01:59,250
You vile scumbag.

39
00:02:01,166 --> 00:02:03,875
I've been worshiping her
blue eyes for all this time!

40
00:02:03,958 --> 00:02:06,916
And then a degenerate like you
takes her away from me?

41
00:02:07,000 --> 00:02:08,833
There is no justice
in this world!

42
00:02:08,916 --> 00:02:10,750
Her eyes are
so incredibly rare.

43
00:02:10,833 --> 00:02:12,625
I spent my whole life
searching for someone

44
00:02:12,708 --> 00:02:14,833
who has eyes like those.

45
00:02:14,916 --> 00:02:19,416
They're alive but dead.
So silent yet so beautiful.

46
00:02:20,666 --> 00:02:24,125
I will never allow you to have
those exquisite peepers.

47
00:02:24,208 --> 00:02:26,875
They belong to me. They're mine!

48
00:02:26,958 --> 00:02:28,958
[heavy breathing]

49
00:02:31,000 --> 00:02:32,958
You think I care
about any of that stuff?

50
00:02:33,041 --> 00:02:36,041
You and I are nothing
like each other.

51
00:02:36,125 --> 00:02:38,041
I don't play this game
for trophies.

52
00:02:38,125 --> 00:02:41,833
But I do know one thing,
she wants me to kill her.

53
00:02:42,958 --> 00:02:45,083
So when it's time
for her to die,

54
00:02:46,166 --> 00:02:47,541
I'm gonna do the deed.

55
00:02:49,125 --> 00:02:50,250
Got it?

56
00:02:50,333 --> 00:02:51,583
What happens to Ray
isn't somethin'

57
00:02:51,666 --> 00:02:53,708
that you get to decide.

58
00:02:53,791 --> 00:02:58,541
So are you saying, Rachel wants
you to be the one to kill her?

59
00:02:58,625 --> 00:03:00,250
[snickers]

60
00:03:00,333 --> 00:03:02,125
Oh, what a relief.

61
00:03:02,208 --> 00:03:04,916
Well, at least now I know
that she's still alive.

62
00:03:05,000 --> 00:03:08,208
The mere fact that you made it
up to this floor only proves it.

63
00:03:09,541 --> 00:03:11,583
Hey, I've got an idea.

64
00:03:11,666 --> 00:03:14,833
How would you like me
to save your pitiful life?

65
00:03:14,916 --> 00:03:18,583
It just so happens that I've got
some medicine with me.

66
00:03:18,666 --> 00:03:20,333
If you agree to a few terms,

67
00:03:20,416 --> 00:03:22,416
I'll use it
to stop the bleeding.

68
00:03:22,500 --> 00:03:24,541
Yeah? And what the hell
do you want?

69
00:03:25,750 --> 00:03:27,625
What I want is
for you to scoop out

70
00:03:27,708 --> 00:03:31,333
Rachel's beautiful peepers
and bring them to me, 'kay?

71
00:03:33,375 --> 00:03:34,916
[ZACK chuckles]

72
00:03:35,000 --> 00:03:37,500
You're one serious sicko,
you know that?

73
00:03:37,583 --> 00:03:39,875
Not gonna happen, doc. No deal.

74
00:03:39,958 --> 00:03:41,500
If I messed up her face,

75
00:03:41,583 --> 00:03:44,333
she'd be even more boring
than she already is.

76
00:03:44,416 --> 00:03:46,875
So I don't really have
much to offer you.

77
00:03:47,833 --> 00:03:50,833
How about you take that medicine
of yours and go to hell?!

78
00:03:52,166 --> 00:03:53,125
[sighs]

79
00:03:53,208 --> 00:03:54,541
Ever the idiot.

80
00:03:56,500 --> 00:03:58,416
Well, I'd better get going now.

81
00:03:58,500 --> 00:04:01,375
Badly hurt or not,
you're still scary.

82
00:04:01,458 --> 00:04:03,000
[groaning]
Hold it!

83
00:04:03,083 --> 00:04:06,375
Or what? You don't have
the strength to chase me.

84
00:04:06,458 --> 00:04:08,083
You wanna find out?

85
00:04:08,166 --> 00:04:09,583
[chuckles]

86
00:04:11,125 --> 00:04:12,083
Hey!

87
00:04:12,166 --> 00:04:14,500
[groaning]

88
00:04:14,583 --> 00:04:16,458
[weakly] Damn you.
Come back here.

89
00:05:49,833 --> 00:05:50,875
[elevator bell dings]

90
00:05:53,041 --> 00:05:54,500
Here we are.

91
00:05:57,375 --> 00:05:59,833
Zack is an honest
and simple soul.

92
00:05:59,916 --> 00:06:03,375
You'll find that much like him,
this floor is uncomplicated.

93
00:06:06,083 --> 00:06:08,333
Go and do
what you came here to do.

94
00:06:14,916 --> 00:06:16,333
[ZACK]
You know, B6.

95
00:06:16,416 --> 00:06:18,625
The one where we first met
and I almost killed ya?

96
00:06:18,708 --> 00:06:21,625
There's somethin' I want you
to bring back here for me.

97
00:06:21,708 --> 00:06:25,791
When you get there, go into
my room and find my knife, okay?

98
00:06:27,458 --> 00:06:28,833
Okay.

99
00:06:52,000 --> 00:06:54,041
[RACHEL]
So, this is Zack's room?

100
00:06:57,583 --> 00:07:01,041
The sofa's torn up.
And the blanket's so thin.

101
00:07:01,125 --> 00:07:02,750
It must've been cold.

102
00:07:06,375 --> 00:07:07,791
Can't use these.

103
00:07:10,500 --> 00:07:12,166
This works, though.

104
00:07:16,041 --> 00:07:17,333
There's no medicine.

105
00:07:20,958 --> 00:07:23,750
He spent all that time
in this awful place?

106
00:07:29,458 --> 00:07:30,416
[gasps]

107
00:07:30,500 --> 00:07:33,750
♪

108
00:07:37,083 --> 00:07:39,250
Is this his handwriting?

109
00:07:39,333 --> 00:07:42,000
-What the hell does it say?
-Isaac Foster.

110
00:07:46,416 --> 00:07:49,083
I really don't know
anything about him, do I?

111
00:07:56,916 --> 00:07:59,958
Hang in there.
I'm coming back for you.

112
00:08:03,083 --> 00:08:05,041
[panting]

113
00:08:05,125 --> 00:08:07,208
Have you completed
your business here?

114
00:08:07,291 --> 00:08:10,500
I have, but I need to
get back to Zack quickly.

115
00:08:10,583 --> 00:08:12,125
As you wish.

116
00:08:12,208 --> 00:08:14,833
There is something
I am curious about, as well.

117
00:08:14,916 --> 00:08:16,541
Let us hurry back.

118
00:08:22,333 --> 00:08:23,375
[elevator bell dings]

119
00:08:26,750 --> 00:08:27,875
Uh?

120
00:08:27,958 --> 00:08:29,208
He's gone.

121
00:08:30,916 --> 00:08:32,708
The suspicious look
that you're giving me

122
00:08:32,791 --> 00:08:34,333
will achieve absolutely nothing.

123
00:08:34,416 --> 00:08:37,916
I've told you, Rachel Gardner.

124
00:08:38,000 --> 00:08:39,500
You are the true cause

125
00:08:39,583 --> 00:08:42,250
of all these
unfortunate occurrences.

126
00:08:42,333 --> 00:08:43,666
What's that supposed to mean?

127
00:08:43,750 --> 00:08:47,208
Did you find Doctor Danny
on the hospital floor?

128
00:08:47,291 --> 00:08:50,166
-Actually...
-He wasn't there, was he?

129
00:08:50,250 --> 00:08:52,333
But I know he died. I saw it.

130
00:08:52,416 --> 00:08:54,416
No, he is still alive.

131
00:08:54,500 --> 00:08:55,833
But I lack an understanding

132
00:08:55,916 --> 00:08:57,791
about his sudden change
in behavior.

133
00:08:58,958 --> 00:09:00,375
Change in behavior?

134
00:09:00,458 --> 00:09:03,250
Danny is a serious
and prudent man.

135
00:09:03,333 --> 00:09:06,833
But for some reason,
he's begun to act strangely.

136
00:09:06,916 --> 00:09:09,958
And my observations suggest
that you are to blame.

137
00:09:10,041 --> 00:09:12,166
Whatever happened to him,
it wasn't my fault.

138
00:09:12,250 --> 00:09:13,666
I need to go
and find Zack now.

139
00:09:13,750 --> 00:09:15,625
I've been studying
your behavior as well.

140
00:09:15,708 --> 00:09:17,333
Huh?

141
00:09:17,416 --> 00:09:19,958
As I watched you throw this
building's gears into disarray,

142
00:09:20,041 --> 00:09:22,416
I took an interest
in your character.

143
00:09:22,500 --> 00:09:25,291
And if you are indeed
exerting a negative influence,

144
00:09:25,375 --> 00:09:27,500
then I must
pass judgment upon you.

145
00:09:29,166 --> 00:09:31,291
At first, watching you search
for the medicine

146
00:09:31,375 --> 00:09:32,708
in order to help Zack

147
00:09:32,791 --> 00:09:34,708
was giving me
the faintest glimmer of hope.

148
00:09:34,791 --> 00:09:37,583
But it would now appear
that hope was all for nothing.

149
00:09:37,666 --> 00:09:40,083
Your subsequent actions
have been self-serving

150
00:09:40,166 --> 00:09:42,125
and without a trace of empathy.

151
00:09:44,375 --> 00:09:45,666
And to make matters worse,

152
00:09:45,750 --> 00:09:47,500
do you remember
what your answer was

153
00:09:47,583 --> 00:09:50,250
when I asked you the reason
why you wished to save Zack?

154
00:09:50,333 --> 00:09:53,708
Losing Zack would be a problem.

155
00:09:53,791 --> 00:09:55,125
A problem?

156
00:09:55,208 --> 00:09:56,708
I'm afraid I don't follow.

157
00:09:56,791 --> 00:10:00,333
Zack swore to God
that he was going to kill me.

158
00:10:00,416 --> 00:10:03,958
If he dies,
he won't be able to.

159
00:10:04,041 --> 00:10:05,000
So, you were...

160
00:10:05,083 --> 00:10:07,208
That's correct, Rachel Gardner.

161
00:10:08,291 --> 00:10:09,958
All of your actions
have been judged

162
00:10:10,041 --> 00:10:11,750
to be of a purely
selfish nature.

163
00:10:11,833 --> 00:10:12,708
[gasps]

164
00:10:12,791 --> 00:10:14,541
That's wrong.

165
00:10:14,625 --> 00:10:16,500
I mean yes, it's true
that I asked Zack

166
00:10:16,583 --> 00:10:18,666
to kill me after
we escape from here.

167
00:10:18,750 --> 00:10:20,333
But it's more than just that.

168
00:10:20,416 --> 00:10:22,041
Zack swore to God
that he would kill me,

169
00:10:22,125 --> 00:10:24,083
so I'm also helping him
keep his word.

170
00:10:25,750 --> 00:10:27,250
Even if, as you said,

171
00:10:27,333 --> 00:10:29,166
Zack did swear to God
to kill you,

172
00:10:29,250 --> 00:10:31,041
do you claim to have
divine knowledge

173
00:10:31,125 --> 00:10:33,125
that God would accept
such a promise?

174
00:10:33,208 --> 00:10:34,875
Let's suppose somebody else

175
00:10:34,958 --> 00:10:36,958
made the exact same vow
that Zack did.

176
00:10:37,041 --> 00:10:38,625
Is it not up to God
to determine

177
00:10:38,708 --> 00:10:40,166
whose promise
will become reality?

178
00:10:41,208 --> 00:10:45,375
And if God's choice goes against
your desires, Rachel Gardner,

179
00:10:45,458 --> 00:10:47,458
would you defy his will?

180
00:10:47,541 --> 00:10:49,291
[shuddering]

181
00:10:51,166 --> 00:10:52,291
Forgive me.

182
00:10:52,375 --> 00:10:54,375
Perhaps that was
a cruel thing to ask.

183
00:10:54,458 --> 00:10:56,500
Now then,
I must make preparations

184
00:10:56,583 --> 00:10:58,458
before I pass final judgment.

185
00:11:00,666 --> 00:11:01,625
More purple smoke?

186
00:11:01,708 --> 00:11:04,291
Ready yourself, Rachel Gardner.

187
00:11:04,375 --> 00:11:07,833
The deliberation over your fate
shall continue.

188
00:11:11,666 --> 00:11:13,375
[RACHEL]
What just happened?

189
00:11:15,416 --> 00:11:17,041
-[hisses]
-[gasps]

190
00:11:17,125 --> 00:11:20,458
♪

191
00:11:23,375 --> 00:11:24,500
[moans]

192
00:11:29,583 --> 00:11:30,791
Zack!

193
00:11:32,458 --> 00:11:33,500
♪

194
00:11:38,833 --> 00:11:41,166
-Look behind you!
-Huh?

195
00:11:41,250 --> 00:11:43,125
-A snake!
-[groans]

196
00:11:43,208 --> 00:11:44,416
Huh?

197
00:11:44,500 --> 00:11:46,833
We have to run! It'll kill you!

198
00:11:46,916 --> 00:11:48,625
-Come on, let's go!
-[ZACK] Hey, wait a second.

199
00:11:48,708 --> 00:11:50,291
Zack, you gotta hurry up!

200
00:11:50,375 --> 00:11:51,666
Chill!

201
00:11:52,916 --> 00:11:54,125
Huh?

202
00:11:55,458 --> 00:11:56,333
[RACHEL]
What just...

203
00:11:56,416 --> 00:11:58,125
Don't "what just" me.

204
00:11:58,208 --> 00:11:59,458
But the giant snake...

205
00:12:00,625 --> 00:12:03,708
There's no giant snake.
You high or somethin'?

206
00:12:03,791 --> 00:12:06,291
You know, I was almost glad
to see you made it back safe,

207
00:12:06,375 --> 00:12:07,875
but now you're sayin'
all this weird shit

208
00:12:07,958 --> 00:12:09,750
and it's really
freakin' me out.

209
00:12:09,833 --> 00:12:13,125
Turns out you can't even handle
the simplest thing by yourself,

210
00:12:13,208 --> 00:12:14,125
can ya?

211
00:12:14,208 --> 00:12:16,291
No, I'm sorry.

212
00:12:16,375 --> 00:12:17,625
-[thuds]
-Huh?

213
00:12:17,708 --> 00:12:19,208
You okay?

214
00:12:20,166 --> 00:12:21,416
Back off.

215
00:12:21,500 --> 00:12:23,375
Why didn't you wait for me
like I said to?

216
00:12:24,541 --> 00:12:26,750
Had company. Lucky me.

217
00:12:26,833 --> 00:12:29,333
Are you talking
about Doctor Danny?

218
00:12:29,416 --> 00:12:30,916
Yeah, how'd you know that?

219
00:12:31,000 --> 00:12:33,250
His body was missing.

220
00:12:33,333 --> 00:12:34,583
Coulda sworn I killed him.

221
00:12:35,916 --> 00:12:37,166
Oh, well.

222
00:12:37,250 --> 00:12:39,916
Main thing is
you came back in one piece.

223
00:12:40,000 --> 00:12:42,791
[shuddering]

224
00:12:42,875 --> 00:12:45,333
-Ugh. Now what?
-I'm sorry.

225
00:12:45,416 --> 00:12:46,916
All the medicine was gone

226
00:12:47,000 --> 00:12:48,958
by the time I got down there
to look for it.

227
00:12:50,375 --> 00:12:52,333
He mentioned somethin'
about that.

228
00:12:52,416 --> 00:12:55,041
Sounds like he took everything
with him to heal himself up.

229
00:12:55,125 --> 00:12:57,000
I guess so.

230
00:12:57,083 --> 00:12:59,708
Did he tell you anything else
that might be helpful?

231
00:13:01,875 --> 00:13:04,208
Nothin' you need
to worry about, kid.

232
00:13:05,250 --> 00:13:06,291
[sighs]

233
00:13:06,375 --> 00:13:08,875
Did you make it
down to my floor?

234
00:13:08,958 --> 00:13:11,458
-Yeah.
-So you picked up the knife?

235
00:13:13,333 --> 00:13:15,125
Aw, hell, yeah!

236
00:13:19,666 --> 00:13:22,791
That's better.
Feels like an old friend.

237
00:13:22,875 --> 00:13:25,583
That knife must be
really important to you.

238
00:13:25,666 --> 00:13:27,541
This was pretty much
the only weapon I had

239
00:13:27,625 --> 00:13:30,458
before I started
usin' the scythe.

240
00:13:30,541 --> 00:13:32,708
All right, let's go.
[groaning]

241
00:13:32,791 --> 00:13:34,375
Wait, you shouldn't
get up right now.

242
00:13:34,458 --> 00:13:36,833
Just mind
your own business, would ya?

243
00:13:36,916 --> 00:13:39,583
I got plenty of rest.
I'll be fine.

244
00:13:39,666 --> 00:13:40,916
Please don't.

245
00:13:41,000 --> 00:13:42,708
What's your problem?

246
00:13:42,791 --> 00:13:45,125
Look, I brought you
some fresh bandages.

247
00:13:45,208 --> 00:13:47,333
So will you let me help you?

248
00:13:48,875 --> 00:13:50,125
Get away!

249
00:13:50,208 --> 00:13:52,625
Don't touch me, all right?
Leave me alone.

250
00:13:59,791 --> 00:14:01,416
It ain't that serious.

251
00:14:01,500 --> 00:14:04,000
Would you quit actin' like
I'm about to drop dead?

252
00:14:05,291 --> 00:14:07,250
What's wrong with you?

253
00:14:07,333 --> 00:14:08,750
You've had a weird look
on your face

254
00:14:08,833 --> 00:14:10,000
ever since you got back.

255
00:14:13,333 --> 00:14:15,750
You remember what that
psycho bitch said, right?

256
00:14:15,833 --> 00:14:18,083
-Down on B3?
-Uh?

257
00:14:18,166 --> 00:14:20,000
I can't tell you how pissed I am

258
00:14:20,083 --> 00:14:22,291
that she turned out
to be right, but she was.

259
00:14:22,375 --> 00:14:24,833
Damn, she really hit
the nail on the head.

260
00:14:24,916 --> 00:14:26,416
You're wrong.

261
00:14:26,500 --> 00:14:28,833
You and I have never been
anybody's tools.

262
00:14:28,916 --> 00:14:30,541
No, not that.

263
00:14:30,625 --> 00:14:32,166
You actually talked me
outta believing

264
00:14:32,250 --> 00:14:34,666
that load of crap
pretty quickly.

265
00:14:34,750 --> 00:14:36,708
Okay, then what was it?

266
00:14:36,791 --> 00:14:39,291
She kept sayin' I was a monster.

267
00:14:39,375 --> 00:14:42,416
But the good news is,
monsters are hard to kill.

268
00:14:43,416 --> 00:14:45,125
You see what I mean?

269
00:14:46,875 --> 00:14:48,666
Hey. Now what's wrong?

270
00:14:48,750 --> 00:14:50,875
All I'm sayin' is that
I'm hard to kill.

271
00:14:50,958 --> 00:14:54,125
So why are you givin' me
that creepy sad face again?

272
00:14:54,208 --> 00:14:55,500
[sighs]

273
00:14:55,583 --> 00:14:56,875
Well, whatever.

274
00:14:56,958 --> 00:14:58,375
If there's no medicine,

275
00:14:58,458 --> 00:15:00,250
I guess I'm just gonna have
to suck it up, right?

276
00:15:01,666 --> 00:15:03,708
You can come with me
if you feel like it.

277
00:15:07,333 --> 00:15:09,125
[RACHEL]
There's a trail of blood.

278
00:15:09,208 --> 00:15:11,333
I guess it belongs
to Doctor Danny.

279
00:15:11,416 --> 00:15:15,041
If he has the medicine,
our best bet is to go after him.

280
00:15:15,125 --> 00:15:17,750
But we don't even have a clue
where the hell he is.

281
00:15:17,833 --> 00:15:19,500
Then we'll just
follow the blood.

282
00:15:19,583 --> 00:15:20,875
Right.

283
00:15:23,166 --> 00:15:24,375
[RACHEL]
Hey, Zack?

284
00:15:24,458 --> 00:15:26,500
[ZACK]
Yeah? What's up?

285
00:15:26,583 --> 00:15:28,000
I have a question.

286
00:15:28,083 --> 00:15:30,750
Since you called yourself
a monster earlier,

287
00:15:30,833 --> 00:15:32,333
does that mean you're not human?

288
00:15:33,375 --> 00:15:34,541
[ZACK sighs]

289
00:15:34,625 --> 00:15:37,000
Well, let me ask you somethin'.

290
00:15:37,083 --> 00:15:39,750
What does it mean
to be human anyway?

291
00:15:39,833 --> 00:15:41,250
I'm not sure.

292
00:15:41,333 --> 00:15:42,916
I mean, is there
somethin' special

293
00:15:43,000 --> 00:15:45,041
all humans are supposed to do?

294
00:15:47,208 --> 00:15:48,708
What God wants, I guess.

295
00:15:48,791 --> 00:15:52,083
Great. This crap again.

296
00:15:52,166 --> 00:15:56,166
Jeez, why does everything always
have to be about God with you?

297
00:15:56,250 --> 00:15:57,875
Whatever.

298
00:15:57,958 --> 00:16:00,375
It's not like I'm worse than
everyone else in this hellhole.

299
00:16:00,458 --> 00:16:02,125
So Who cares what I am?

300
00:16:02,208 --> 00:16:04,291
Oh, wait, I know what it is.

301
00:16:04,375 --> 00:16:06,208
You're afraid your God's
gonna be mad at you

302
00:16:06,291 --> 00:16:08,583
for lettin' yourself be killed
by a monster, aren't ya?

303
00:16:08,666 --> 00:16:11,750
No! You can't say that!
It's not true!

304
00:16:13,375 --> 00:16:14,583
[sighs]

305
00:16:15,583 --> 00:16:17,958
You don't have to get
that bent outta shape.

306
00:16:19,125 --> 00:16:22,458
Ugh. Why didn't I just keep
my stupid mouth shut?

307
00:16:22,541 --> 00:16:24,333
Come on, let's go.

308
00:16:25,333 --> 00:16:28,500
One more question. Last one.

309
00:16:28,583 --> 00:16:30,166
That room where
I found the knife,

310
00:16:30,250 --> 00:16:32,041
was that where
you had been living?

311
00:16:32,125 --> 00:16:33,500
What difference does that make?

312
00:16:34,750 --> 00:16:37,208
I was just curious, that's all.

313
00:16:37,291 --> 00:16:38,625
Yeah?

314
00:16:39,791 --> 00:16:42,000
You made me realize something.

315
00:16:42,083 --> 00:16:44,791
There's a lot I still don't know
about you and your past.

316
00:16:44,875 --> 00:16:47,125
So I guess I was just hoping

317
00:16:47,208 --> 00:16:48,625
that you would share
some things with me.

318
00:16:48,708 --> 00:16:50,250
Seriously, Ray?

319
00:16:50,333 --> 00:16:51,958
Do you even hear yourself?

320
00:16:52,041 --> 00:16:55,666
It's just... I think, maybe,

321
00:16:55,750 --> 00:16:57,833
that room could be
a little bit cleaner, you know?

322
00:16:57,916 --> 00:16:59,833
[grunts]
Are you kidding?

323
00:16:59,916 --> 00:17:02,291
I'm never goin' back there,
so who gives a damn?

324
00:17:11,083 --> 00:17:13,000
[gasps]

325
00:17:13,083 --> 00:17:15,291
Somethin' wrong?

326
00:17:15,375 --> 00:17:16,916
[hisses]

327
00:17:17,916 --> 00:17:19,125
[gasps]

328
00:17:21,458 --> 00:17:22,375
Careful.

329
00:17:22,458 --> 00:17:24,375
Hey, would you get off your ass?

330
00:17:24,458 --> 00:17:26,666
See if there's a way outta here.

331
00:17:26,750 --> 00:17:27,875
Got it.

332
00:17:31,875 --> 00:17:32,916
[grunts]

333
00:17:35,208 --> 00:17:36,791
Okay. Here's an exit.

334
00:17:36,875 --> 00:17:38,375
Be right there.

335
00:17:46,291 --> 00:17:48,250
[RACHEL]
Quick, before it comes back.

336
00:17:53,125 --> 00:17:54,250
[gasps]

337
00:17:54,333 --> 00:17:57,000
[grunting]

338
00:17:57,083 --> 00:17:58,333
-[hisses]
-[gasps]

339
00:18:04,541 --> 00:18:05,708
Zack?

340
00:18:05,791 --> 00:18:07,791
[ZACK]
I've had enough of this shit.

341
00:18:08,875 --> 00:18:12,250
I'm so exhausted,
I can barely use my scythe.

342
00:18:12,333 --> 00:18:15,000
Don't ever make me
do that again, Ray.

343
00:18:15,083 --> 00:18:16,458
Time to go.

344
00:18:20,166 --> 00:18:22,166
[ZACK groaning]

345
00:18:29,708 --> 00:18:31,666
Zack, you can't keep
going like this.

346
00:18:31,750 --> 00:18:33,708
If you don't stop, you'll die.

347
00:18:33,791 --> 00:18:35,333
Oh, please.

348
00:18:35,416 --> 00:18:37,708
Takes more than that
to kill a monster.

349
00:18:37,791 --> 00:18:41,500
Come on. Be still.
You have to.

350
00:18:41,583 --> 00:18:44,875
I don't know what this face
is about, but I don't like it.

351
00:18:44,958 --> 00:18:46,916
What face?

352
00:18:47,000 --> 00:18:49,958
Anyway, stay here.
I'll find the doctor.

353
00:18:50,041 --> 00:18:52,833
Then I can bring back
some medicine for you.

354
00:18:52,916 --> 00:18:54,833
No. I'm serious.

355
00:18:54,916 --> 00:18:56,291
What the hell's
come over you?

356
00:18:56,375 --> 00:18:57,708
Huh?

357
00:18:57,791 --> 00:19:00,625
Tellin' me to rest
and tryin' to bandage me up.

358
00:19:00,708 --> 00:19:04,291
-I just...
-And lookin' at me all gloomy.

359
00:19:04,375 --> 00:19:07,083
Somethin' musta happened
to make you feel guilty.

360
00:19:07,166 --> 00:19:09,375
Well, no. It's just...

361
00:19:09,458 --> 00:19:10,916
Spit it out.

362
00:19:11,000 --> 00:19:13,041
I have to get
that medicine.

363
00:19:13,125 --> 00:19:16,250
Answer my friggin'
question, already.

364
00:19:16,333 --> 00:19:18,208
Besides, if you go
after him alone,

365
00:19:18,291 --> 00:19:19,333
you're dead meat.

366
00:19:19,416 --> 00:19:21,875
I still have the gun.

367
00:19:21,958 --> 00:19:23,791
If I run into him,
I'll shoot him.

368
00:19:23,875 --> 00:19:26,500
Let me see that thing.

369
00:19:26,583 --> 00:19:27,916
Give it.

370
00:19:40,791 --> 00:19:42,125
Bang.

371
00:19:46,416 --> 00:19:48,625
Now, what did you think
you were gonna do with a gun

372
00:19:48,708 --> 00:19:51,500
that doesn't even have
any bullets in it?

373
00:19:51,583 --> 00:19:53,166
Don't be stupid.

374
00:19:53,250 --> 00:19:56,708
You wouldn't last five minutes
alone with that basket case.

375
00:19:56,791 --> 00:19:59,375
Ya want me to be the one
who kills you, right?

376
00:20:00,541 --> 00:20:02,666
And yet still,
for some reason,

377
00:20:02,750 --> 00:20:05,291
all you can think about is
whether I'm gonna survive.

378
00:20:05,375 --> 00:20:07,958
Who cares which
one of us murders ya?

379
00:20:08,041 --> 00:20:09,541
You're gonna die either way.

380
00:20:11,375 --> 00:20:12,875
I care, Zack.

381
00:20:12,958 --> 00:20:15,208
Because you swore to God
that you'd kill me.

382
00:20:15,291 --> 00:20:17,583
♪

383
00:20:17,666 --> 00:20:19,000
[sighs]

384
00:20:19,083 --> 00:20:21,083
Oh, yeah, that. I forgot.

385
00:20:22,333 --> 00:20:24,666
Are you sure it's a good idea
to take my word for it?

386
00:20:24,750 --> 00:20:26,583
I am a monster, after all.

387
00:20:27,625 --> 00:20:29,708
You said you hate liars, right?

388
00:20:29,791 --> 00:20:33,250
More than anything.
And a broken promise is a lie.

389
00:20:33,333 --> 00:20:34,541
-Then--
-But listen.

390
00:20:34,625 --> 00:20:36,916
Here's the thing, Ray.

391
00:20:37,000 --> 00:20:38,541
There is no God
in this world.

392
00:20:38,625 --> 00:20:39,625
[gasps]

393
00:20:39,708 --> 00:20:42,083
[bell rings, fades]

394
00:20:43,583 --> 00:20:46,166
-[voice breaking] You're wrong.
-Huh?

395
00:20:46,250 --> 00:20:49,041
If there's no God, then...

396
00:20:50,125 --> 00:20:52,333
how am I supposed to go on?

397
00:20:52,416 --> 00:20:54,375
Listen, just because
you swore to God

398
00:20:54,458 --> 00:20:57,083
that you would kill me,
that isn't the only reason.

399
00:20:57,166 --> 00:21:01,166
Even if somebody else had made
the exact same promise to me,

400
00:21:01,250 --> 00:21:03,083
it still wouldn't
have been good enough.

401
00:21:03,166 --> 00:21:05,791
Okay, then why?

402
00:21:05,875 --> 00:21:08,750
Um, because...

403
00:21:08,833 --> 00:21:10,833
I don't know. I'm sorry.

404
00:21:12,000 --> 00:21:15,333
Damn it, every time I think you
can't be any more screwed up.

405
00:21:16,791 --> 00:21:18,791
Can you smile?

406
00:21:18,875 --> 00:21:20,291
I can't, okay?

407
00:21:20,375 --> 00:21:22,208
I'm just not very good
at smiling.

408
00:21:22,291 --> 00:21:24,708
Trust me, I know
damn well you suck at it.

409
00:21:24,791 --> 00:21:26,166
Just do it.

410
00:21:37,125 --> 00:21:38,750
I'm gonna go to sleep.

411
00:21:38,833 --> 00:21:40,500
You do whatever
the hell you want.

412
00:21:47,375 --> 00:21:48,583
[gasps]

413
00:21:52,458 --> 00:21:55,625
Hey. Take this.

414
00:21:55,708 --> 00:21:58,041
I don't know
if you'll be able to use it,

415
00:21:58,125 --> 00:22:00,333
but maybe it'll come in handy.

416
00:22:00,416 --> 00:22:01,375
[groans]

417
00:22:05,791 --> 00:22:07,458
Thank you.

418
00:22:07,541 --> 00:22:09,875
And I promise I'll be useful.

419
00:22:15,333 --> 00:22:18,208
♪

420
00:23:45,416 --> 00:23:49,916
♪

